TextBlock.TextLine: Adij 29 April 1697
brussel pierre niclaes parboms
ick hebbe op 23 deser ul staelen gesonden van 12 fijne lakens en oievoor
ul reeckennge gepresenteert miets betaelende den eersten en incoop
a 37 & 3 p. cte voor assurantie hebbe geen antwort becomen is ul die
conditie niet aengenaem, sal om ul te animeeren de 3p. C voor
gslasantie cederen & alleen mij met de winst vergenoegen tot 37
en soo ul het selve soo niet accepteert soo bidde laet mij wetenost
gij die voor mijn reeekeninge niet vercoopen, want anders soude ick de
selve aen een ander senden, omdat men hier wijnich fijn goet vercoopt
dul versoecke een letter antwort ter wijlen blijve
Leeds thomas potter
th
R may 1697
mij last to you on y 25 past carried order & instruction for 36 Jmsh
desens to bee made up in 3 packes as alsoo go white bayes inone
pack, where by pteck please to provide, so white kersies 30 sty 30
of Abram intey y half & the rest such like, not worse, to bee sentto
hull for the forst convoij for holland now have before mee yours
of 16 march 8 posts beinge come together, for the charges of £19:5:3
you have credit & seinge that fine dosens from N 4 to 3ƒ raw
are a scheape, as they can bee, & the holland fleet beinge gone, &
that buyinge for hamb: will bee ended in 20 dayes, & what is more
that you iugde the lattes, end of Aprill, to bee goed time to buy, so
expect, these mj orders, sshall reach y.s handes for the best markett
you make no mention of what you have disposed by m. Bollangere
I have remitt: hera in all £366:15: 4 where of hee is that har
es provision & charges we can not come to top. to so ordered hin
to fallow your order with the ballance dew to mee, whilst I shalllenm
you my remises dirteely, payable in milt monney or quinees, wheres
you my depend for next week, when you send patt. oft the clothes
bought, lest them bee made on a paper a part, as 6i9 againe, as
them you send, because wee pay no port for them & wee want
them so shew to our customers, so that s'is un propre, to finde
them on yeu invoyces please to advise what passes from time totime
principalley about the new wooll to & take mij measures accordingy
£366:15:4 is all ghave & had re mens
London walter & Will: kent hellenger & you make no meurn et
ythharl dissased, so rake yo mea sures
Jaccorda 2 maij
mj last to you was on the 25: past, sence 8 postes come, thereby yu
th
23: march, 20 ditto & P: April N. 9 was all that I see time hath
ermitted to ship by this convoy, because all the vessels where gone
non, beinge in the swaille, attendeinge for winde & that theij haveone
can of wars, of 48 guns, for their convoij to the downes where they
all have 6 man of warr of ostend, I wish they were well over al alloo
hose for holland for those of dunkerque are fitteinge out all what sen
hey can, to sett John bait att sea with en esquadre wch is to connan
els de so manney kapers as now are, every where about, tis jours
dinion on the 23 march, that in 4 months goods maij bee bought
heaper & better made of wch one month is all ready past & they suppoe
haf wee shall not have an othes convoij, before july of August here fore
ake the best measures you to bus to goods ordered 25: past to wek
ost bee added some clothes to the inclosed patt. send you also a
memorandam for that I desire bought for the first cnvoy convoyel
for w please to take the best measures, that can vee done to have 16s
the best and cheapest goods and further in all acteinge as for the self for
d the great risico & kigh ex. is cause that wee have greet pams to advance
on the risie goods, wee are all de ceaved in your exspectation of a sall ofex.
because everij one beleaved, that the great remises must cause a fall
of ex. where upon everij one wweld not give, though bils have been
presented at N34:11 2ock now yalƒ 35:6, so that s see, that I may de lay
net langer to remitt you as spromise you to send considerabeley within
this & 14 dayes for I have meare £10000:- readdij & hath this good
while, & could not resolve to so high ex. af now I must do for
I would not have drauwen upon mee, where I can advance 3 a 4 p. 19
bij remitteinge, your say mij pack of cotton remains of mij order
s suppose you will not finde anney order this yeare for cottons for
mee, except t'bee to wrapp the packes, there fore if them goods
come cheapes within a month or 2 as serpect, to these mij not bee
for my accompt, further thus memorandum is all what I delire
bee bought in exspectation to knouw what passes remaine
Amst. geraert rover
Adij Bmay 1691
ben ul danckbaer voor duwe van 25 & 26 passato sedert hebben wij dan 8 poster
van engelant becomen waernevens de wissel in een doen blijft niet tegenstaende
men hier seght datter groote remises voor d'engelsche sijn overgecomen die
bestaen in court gelt te betaelen, het schijnt de soden aen dit werck geracht
sijn & uijtgevonden hebben sonder de wissel te altereren depeningen te foernier e
nie can ick niet wel langer dillaiygeeren derrewachhtss te remitteeren, over sulck
geerne verneme hoe het costij sich sal draegen, ick vreese dese continueel
coste winden nons noch mochte schade doen, dat men schrijft van dunckersen
dat men daer onophoudelijck doende is om Jan bart met een esquadre in
see te brengen, goot wel ons voor verliesen bewaeren, sal de doort vanden
coninck van sweeden het werck vanden vrede niet seer verachteren iets
particuliers voor vallende versocke te wete & expeditie aen d'ingeslotene
London charlas Bollengiere
2 maij
den ul van 2o februgry lest op sijnen tijde & dien van 23 meert maer
voor gisteren ontfangen om datter & posten te samen sijn aengecomen die
door de noch continueerde ooste avinden aen ul sij de worden opgehouden, waer
door vwij onse convoijen niet overkrijgen, godt wil geven sij behouden mogen over
comen omdat sonder de menich valdigecapers van denckereken. noch in sel met g
alle spoot een iew esquader voor Jan boort wort geprepareert het welcke soo
danige ongelegentheden inde negotie couseert dat mij best dunck wat stil
te staen & alleen geraetsaen gevonden hebbe tot dat het vreede is meester potter
is meckelijck te comitteeren, deralven gelieft hem het nitto van mijne avance
in ul handen te laeten uijtvolgen, afcortende ul provisie & oncosten omonse
reeckening daer mede tot daer toe te sluyten, opt hope dat den vreede haert volgen
maght om met meerder animo de negotie te vernieuwen en onse kenisse te
